The wood in the waves copies the window frames, rails, decorative elements of the doors, cuckoos and rails.
House Batlló, which is located in the Eixample district on Passeig de Grácia shopping street No. 43, was rebuilt by architect Emilio Sala Cortes from 1877.
The reconstruction took place for two years and the house was completed in 1906.
The investor, the wealthy industrialist Josep Batlló, originally insisted on demolishing the old building and building a completely new one, but soon Gaudí's idea for an unusual and cheaper reconstruction.
Casa Batlló, however, did not design Antoni Gaudí himself.
The architect Josep Maria Jujol worked with him.
It was on his designer board that decorations were created for the representative apartment of the owner of the property and the use of mosaic on the facade.
A number of other artists and artists also worked on the facade.
