The bizarre may seem their 45-degree slope.
In the work of Gaudí, he did not respect the building regulations at that time and did not let them bind.
At the beginning of the construction, he obtained a building permit from the city, but the information on the planned reconstruction was so vague that two years later, when finishing, the city council was reinstated and applied for correction.
For example, the councilman was concerned about the fact that the construction was also affecting the pillars in the public pavement.
There has never been a remedy, on the contrary: only 15 days after the challenge of the city section, Josep Batlló requested (and successfully obtained) permission to rent the top two floors of the building.
