In the gallery on the second floor there was a lounge and on the third floor a bedroom and a private part of the apartment.
The ground floor was rented jewelry store.
The entire six-storey house crosses the stairs, which can be climbed up to the roof terrace itself.
The main elements of the reconstruction were the removal of all right angles and direct lines and their replacement with curved walls.
Gaudí also worked with a modern concept of connecting space.
The social part can be completely connected by opening the living room doors and the larger society can communicate comfortably without, at the same time, maintaining the privacy needed for more intimate conversations.
In addition to the new facade, the house with Gaudí's reconstruction also gained a unique roof and two extra floors.
Gaudí's game with light, blue and white glazed tiles is also impressive, with which the inner courtyard and lights are placed.
The game of two colors adds maximum light in all floors of the house.
Just bet on the principle that white reflects light more than dark, which, on the contrary, absorbs sunlight.
