And here Germany has a radically new vision of what his future is supposed to be like, which runs counter to the idea of respecting the old traditions that a large part of the other members hold on to.
Faced with European opposition, Germany is beginning to speculate on three possible paths from the crisis.
The first one is a strong euro area, which would include Germany, but also Austria or the Netherlands, for example, while the southern states would leave the monetary zone.
The second is the return to Mark - although it may now appear like a scifi, this version has broad public support, close to 50% of the population.
The third possibility is, according to the German proposals, to re-work the euro with greater macroeconomic surveillance, budgetary severity, fines for guilty countries, possible deferrals of payments for some of them, and to extend the possible costs of regulation to the private sector.
