The United States amends the rules on the issue of visas
People will have to contact the Centres of Services for Visa Applicants before the interview at the Consular Department; the costs will be lower and the waiting time will be reduced.
As from 10 January 2011, the process of discussing visas will change to the United States Embassy and consulate.
With the new procedure, most applicants will have to contact the Centres of Services for Visa Applicants (shortly from English ASC) before the interview at the Consular Department.
The staff of the ASC shall collect biometric information from the applicant and shall be evaluated before the interview by the Consular Department.
The new procedure will have certain advantages, among which the following are calculated:
The total costs of processing the visa will be lower, no longer a fee will be paid for agreeing a meeting, the second for processing the application and the other for delivery of the transport document.
The applicant shall pay only a single fee covering all three services.
The current tariff will remain unchanged: $140 for a tourist visa, $150 for visa cases with applications (including temporary staff visas) and $390 for a visa for traders and investors.
People who wish to renew their visa will not have to have an interview with a consular officer, but will only turn to the nearest ASC, where they will submit their documents and fingerprints will be taken.
Given that biometric information will be collected in the ASC, applicants who will require a second meeting with the Consular Division will spend less time here than in the past.
Likewise, those who will apply for a visa at the consulate in Ciudad Juárez, Monterrey and Nuevo Laredo will no longer pay an extra fee for the service of 26 dollars.
For further information on the new visa application procedure, visit the following website: http://mexico.usmbassy.gov/boletines/sp101201_Visas-FAQs.html
